{
  "answer": "**Yama Smṛti (also known as Yama Smṛti), Chapter 2.**\n\nThis Sanskrit Dharmaśāstra text, attributed to Yama, prescribes these fines in two consecutive verses amid rules on merchants' adulterations of groceries and oils:\n\n> Ghee sold mixed with sesame oil under the name of ghee, / the merchant shall be made to pay four times the value; or oil mixed with ghee. // YSS_2.37 //[^1]\n\n> Pepper with stone fragments, salt with earth, / and asafoetida with tree resin—he shall likewise be made to pay four times the value. // YSS_2.38 //[^2]\n\n[^1]: Yama Smṛti, [paragraph](/works/unknown-yama-smrti-552f8d/02/translation/#p-551495).\n[^2]: Yama Smṛti, [paragraph](/works/unknown-yama-smrti-552f8d/02/translation/#p-6039eb).",
